Tolerate missing stack-pointer global in Interpreter

When wasm-bindgen-cli's descriptor interpreter runs against an
Emscripten-emitted wasm, the stack-pointer global's initializer is not a
plain `ConstExpr::Value(I32/I64)` so the global isn't snapshotted into
`self.globals` by the loop at the top of `Interpreter::new`. The later
`self.globals[&sp]` lookup in `interpret_descriptor` panics with
`no entry found for key`.

This patch defaults the stack-pointer initial value to 0 when the
global is missing, and skips the round-trip assert in the same case.
Descriptor functions only push numbers onto the wasm-bindgen-side
descriptor list and don't touch the stack pointer in practice, so the
default is safe.

Upstream-able: this is the kind of resilience that would also help
other wasm-toolchain combinations (custom linkers, future Emscripten
versions). Submit to wasm-bindgen if this works end-to-end.

--- a/crates/cli-support/src/interpreter/mod.rs
+++ b/crates/cli-support/src/interpreter/mod.rs
@@ -202,7 +202,7 @@ impl Interpreter {
         self.stopped = false;

         if let Some(sp) = self.stack_pointer {
-            self.stack_pointer_initial = self.globals[&sp];
+            self.stack_pointer_initial = self.globals.get(&sp).copied().unwrap_or(0);
         }

         let func = module.funcs.get(id);
@@ -212,7 +212,9 @@ impl Interpreter {

         // Validate the stack pointer was restored to its value at function entry.
         if let Some(sp) = self.stack_pointer {
-            assert_eq!(self.globals[&sp], self.stack_pointer_initial);
+            if let Some(actual) = self.globals.get(&sp) {
+                assert_eq!(*actual, self.stack_pointer_initial);
+            }
         }
         &self.descriptor
     }
